social_posts.post_text: The way that silk moves with the wind is synonymous with the energy of women 🤍 || A beautiful and rainy afternoon in Laguna Beach with Christy.

Introducing: Love Letter to Oregon - My 2022 Print Shop. I’m so happy to share this collection with y’all. The landscape of this place continues to inspire me in so many ways. From the high desert in the east to the lush seascapes to the west. Oregon is a dreamland. Aiming to make these prints as budget friendly as possible, I’ve included shipping in the cost.  I’m offering two sizes: 8.5x11 and 11x14. To those who order, I hope you love them as much as I do and I am honored to have my work in your home.❤️

Photos walks around LA are truly the best way to slow the city down and see all the beauty. The way light hits the buildings, casting long shadows leading up to a stranger on a street corner. Peering down colorful alleyways painted yellow and pink. The height of the palms swaying in the Santa Ana winds. The smell of the food trucks down the street that make you salivate. These are all romantic things about LA and a reminder you can find beauty in the details. #madewithkodak

A rainy day in Yellowstone ☁️ #35mm

(1/2) The day was hot. A heatwave blanketed Oregon as the sounds of plates and glasses clinked together, being laid out on the table in anticipation for guests. Angie moved about the kitchen preparing the menu, making sure every detail was accounted for. Friends started pouring in, offering assistance wherever it was needed, proving early on how special the community surrounding @comparta_ truly is. The sounds of knives meeting the cutting board, water rinsing the vegetables, and shuffling of feet filled the kitchen. Guests began trickling in, taking their seats, exchanging names as well as laughter. The heat of the late summer day settled in the backyard only offering relief when the darkness grew and the candles were lit. As each course made its way to the table, all I could hear was a dance of “wows” and “oh my gods”. A delicious array of foods all surrounding the beauty of community. A perfect night.

You truly never know what to expect on the Oregon coast. The conditions are constantly changing - from sun to fog to rain back to sun. The same goes for wildlife. An abundance of species call this place home and we were sooo very lucky to see the resident elk make their way down onto the beach to play and soak in the salt water. All I had on me was my little (but trusty) 35mm point and shoot and a few frames left on the roll. The herd was so comfortable existing here which makes me happy to see how humans and wild animals can coexist and respect the space. I love this coastline and all of its magic. #madewithkodak #35mm
